				<li id="15790105" class="cmnt-root" data="11" data-d="1466363603000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t530042/Twinkling-Dragon-Head-Stone" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">19 Jun 2016 15:13</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=165&p=15790105" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">A lot of you wondered (myself included) why you were not given the Hawkwards Swordglass when you spoke to the smith, even though you had the twinkling torso. Here is the reason: you weren&apos;t far enough along in Hawkwoods quest to do so. You have to get him to leave the shrine in the first place. They way you do that is to make sure that the Abyss Watchers, Curse-Rotted Greatwood, Deacons of the Deep and the Crystal Sage have been defeated. Then go exhaust Hawkwoods dialogue, go TP to another bornfire, TP back, exhaust his dialogue... repeat this untill he suddenly has disappeared from firelink shrine. Now you can go talk to the smith, and he will greet you with a new message.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-15790105" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-15790105" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>11</p>